        public LocationsManager.CreateLocationOptions setLocationType(int type)
        Set location type. This parameter is provided for clients as a means of identifying what kind of location this is. For example, an application may want to save gas stations to the address book. In this case, the client can save its internal type identifier for "gas station" to the locationType field.

        public LocationsManager.CreateLocationOptions setOrder(int order)
